    <stitle>FULL POWER HYDRAULIC ABS BRAKE SYSTEM - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl04050300">
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The full power brakes system operates in two different main modes: normal braking and ABS braking. On
                vehicles equipped with optional Automatic Traction Control (ATC) a third mode (ATC) exists. In general,
                the HCU ECU monitors the wheel speed sensors and other system parameters to determine which operational
                mode is necessary.
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0405016">FIGURE 16</hotlnk>
                shows a physical representation of the brake system hydraulic and electrical circuits.
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0405017">FIGURE 17</hotlnk>
                shows the hydraulic circuits within the HCU in detail. It is important to note that the relay valves are
                hydraulically controlled while all of the other valves are electronically controlled solenoid valves. In
                this section we will describe how the components of the system control the foundation brakes during each
                of the three operational modes.
            </para>
